  "prompt": "What is the Lewis dot structure of C2H3Cl?",
  "response": "To draw the Lewis dot structure for C2H3Cl (chloroethylene), follow these steps:\n\n1. Determine the total number of valence electrons:\n   - Carbon (C) has 4 valence electrons, there are 2 carbons: \\(2 \\times 4 = 8\\)\n   - Hydrogen (H) has 1 valence electron, there are 3 hydrogens: \\(3 \\times 1 = 3\\)\n   - Chlorine (Cl) has 7 valence electrons\n   Total valence electrons: \\(8 + 3 + 7 = 18\\)\n\n2. Determine the arrangement of atoms:\n   The typical structure for C2H3Cl is two carbon atoms double-bonded to each other, with each carbon forming additional single bonds with hydrogen and chlorine as needed.\n\n3. Form the skeleton structure:\n   Draw the carbon-carbon bond. Then add hydrogen and chlorine atoms:\n   \\[\n   H_2C = C - H \\rightarrow H_2C - C - H\\]\n   Add chlorine to one of the carbons:\n   \\[\n   H_2C = C - H \\rightarrow H_2C = C - H\n       |\n       Cl\n    \n\n4. Distribute the valence electrons:\n   Each bond represents two shared electrons. Place these shared electron pairs around the atoms while satisfying the duet rule for hydrogen (2 electrons) and the octet rule for carbon and chlorine (8 electrons each).\n\n5. Complete the structure with remaining electrons:\n   After drawing bonds:\n   \\[\n   H-\\und C-\\und Cl\n   \\]\n   Finish by adding remaining electrons:\n   On the left carbon:\n   \\[\n    6+1\\rightarrow 8, complete according to octet rule\n    \\]\n    and double check\n   \\[\n   H\u2212\\und C=\\und H\n   olecule\n    \\]\n   \nThe final Lewis dot structure should look like this:\n```\n      H\n       |\n   H - C = C - H\n       |\n       Cl\n```\n\nEach carbon has a full octet, with carbon-carbon bond sharing 4 electrons total.\n",
